    <taskbody>

		<section>
			<p>The <uicontrol>Control Bar</uicontrol> is visible to <term>administrators</term> and <term>hosts</term>. <!-- See <xref format="dita" scope="peer" href="../../content-managers/building-your-site/copy-design-to-child-pages-via-persona-bar.dita">Copy the Page's Design to Its Child Pages via the Persona Bar</xref> as a content manager. --></p>
		</section>

        <steps>
            <step><cmd>Go to the parent page.</cmd></step>

            <step>
				<cmd>Go to <menucascade><uicontrol>Edit Page</uicontrol> <uicontrol>Page Appearance</uicontrol></menucascade>.</cmd>
				<info>
					<image scalefit="yes" placement="break" align="left" href="../../common/img/scr-menuEditPagePageAppearance.png"><alt>Edit Page - Page Appearance</alt></image>
				</info>
            </step>

			<step>
				<cmd>Under the <uicontrol>Advanced Settings</uicontrol> tab, look for <uicontrol>Copy design to descendants</uicontrol>, and click/tap the <uicontrol>Copy design</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
				<info>
					<image scalefit="yes" placement="break" align="left" href="../../common/img/scr-PageAppearance-CopyDesign.png"><alt>Advanced Settings - Copy design to descendants - Copy design</alt></image>
				</info>
			</step>

			<step><cmd>Confirm.</cmd></step>

        </steps>

    </taskbody>

</task>
